        <p>You can specify that thumbnail images should be shown while you are editing the content. This is simply a feature for you as the author, allowing you to scale all images down to 48 pixels high (if the original size is larger than that). This lets you see more content and less of your images as you edit topics. The images are only scaled for your editing purposes; they are not <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive">necessarily </MadCap:conditionalText>shown as thumbnails in the output.</p>
